foliation.note: Numbering in pencil in the upper right-hand corner of the first leaf recto of each quire (except for quire 1), possibly by M.R. James. Full foliation added after digitisation.

collation.p: The manuscript comprises twenty-three quires composed mostly of eight leaves. Quire 14 is made of 6 leaves, initial and final quires of four leaves. The last leaf of the final quire is used as a pastedown.

list.item: Quire a4 (ff. i-iii: first leaf missing)
Quire b4 (ff. 163-165: last leaf used as pastedown)

signatures.p: First six quires are signed on recto of first leaf and verso of the last leaf in a contemporary hand. Remaining quires are signed in a modern hand in pencil on recto of first leaf.

binding.p: Original alum-tawed skin over wooden boards sewn on four bands slightly raised on the flat spine. Mark of a strap on original front cover and clasp on original back cover.

history.acquisition: Given to Queens' College Library in the early 1630s by Francis Tyndall Tyndall, Francis with a 17th-century inscription recording the gift on f. ii recto: 'Donum Francisci Tindall armigeri'.

recordHist.source: This catalogue entry draws on the description in M.R. James, A descriptive catalogue of the western manuscripts in the library of Queens’ College, Cambridge (Cambridge, 1905).

availability.p: For further information on the availability of the manuscript, please contact Queens' Old Library and Special Collections.

layout.seg: Two columns, 37 lines, frame and lines ruled in brown leadpoint. Pricked in the outer margins. Written above top line.

decoNote.p: Plain initial (N, 2. ll.) in red (ii verso); green initial (Q, 4 ll.) with red flourishing (iii recto). Most of the spaces left for initials are blank.

additions.note: List of chapters on f. i recto in a 13/14th-century hand: 'Capitulatio siue series liber Genesios'.
Occasional marginal notes and nota marks in ink an early hand; occasional manicules and marginalia in a later hand in pencil.
